title: For Sale:  Model 1898, 30/40 Krag
postcontent: US Springfield Armory model: 1898 serial # 196153 (manufactured in 1899).  Overall length: 49”. Barrel length: 30” weight: 9 lbs.Pressed into the dark wood above the trigger guard is a small rectangle with squared-off corners, containing a cursive script JSA and the year 1903.The J, the S and the A are the initials of master armorer J. Sumner Adams, showing the rifle had been accepted for use by the US government.Also, just to the rear of the trigger guard is the ‘Proof Mark’ stamping (letter “P” in cursive): inside a ½” diameter circle.  The rifle is in excellent working order.  The rear sight (with all of its adjustments) works as  though it was new.  The bolt action is butter smooth with no play.  I have a copy of the original manual as a *.PDF file.  Rifle comes with it's original US Springfield Krag Cleaning Rod Set & Oiler (3 Rods, 2 Plain, 1 Slotted & 1 Oiler).  The leather rifle sling (albeit old), is not the original sling.     RARE Spanish America War Era US Army Leather McKeever Cartridge Box for .30-40 Krag Cartridges.  The leather (and interior canvas) is in good condition.  No cracks or crazing.  Nice US marking on the front.  The interior canvas cartridge pockets are also in Excellent Condition. They are not streched out or torn, as is common, in these boxes.  The edge of the box is stamped "Rock Island Arsenal 1910  T.C.C."  Additional stamping on leather catch: "A-10".  This is a very hard to find pre-WWI era cartridge box.     Original Spanish-American War era Model 1892 bayonet with correct all-metal scabbard. Made by the Springfield Arsenal and armory-dated 1903.  This bayonet's blade is just slightly used with the correct bright-white original finish remaining; the blade has original blunt edge as it was released from an arsenal; it hasn't been sharpened; the tip is intact. All surfaces have an attractive light-gray patina throughout. Original wood handle scales.  All handle parts are tight with zero play. The scabbard/bayonet release mechanism within the handle is in excellent working order and 100% functional. Ricasso is date-stamped 1903 on one side and US on the other. The bayonet is about 16-1/4" / 41.3 cm overall; the blade is about 11-5/8" / 29.5 cm long.  This bayonet has not been cleaned or tampered with in any way; 100% original condition.Please email me for a lot more pictures.  REDACTED
